      • sharedMemoryReads

        public long sharedMemoryReads()
        Gets the total number of requests received by the service through the shared memory of the DPE. This is the number of all requests received since the service was deployed.

        A service uses the shared memory to receive requests from services running in the same DPE. For requests received from services in other DPEs and orchestrators see bytesRecv.

        Returns:
        the accumulated number of requests received through the shared memory

      • sharedMemoryWrites

        public long sharedMemoryWrites()
        Gets the total number of requests sent by the service through the shared memory of the DPE. This is the number of all requests sent since the service was deployed.

        A service uses the shared memory to send requests to services running in the same DPE. For requests sent to services in other DPEs and orchestrators see bytesSent.

        Returns:
        the accumulated number of requests sent through the shared memory

      • bytesReceived

        public long bytesReceived()
        Gets the total amount of bytes received by the service through the network. This is the sum of the size of all messages received by the service since it was deployed.

        A service receives network messages from services running in other DPEs, and orchestrators. For messages received from services in the same DPE see sharedMemoryReads().

        Returns:
        the accumulated amount of bytes received through the network

      • bytesSent

        public long bytesSent()
        Gets the total amount of bytes sent by the service through the network. This is the sum of the size of all messages published by the service since it was deployed.

        A service publishes network messages to services running in other DPEs, and orchestrators. For messages sent to services in the same DPE see sharedMemoryWrites().

        Returns:
        the accumulated amount of bytes sent through the network

      • executionTime

        public long executionTime()
        Gets the total execution time of the service. This is the sum of the execution time of all requests processed by the service since it was deployed.
        Returns:
        the accumulated execution time, in microseconds
